Alonso on Gerrard: &quot;I remember my first days in Liverpool. He was a true leader by example, not just in words, you had to watch and learn.&quot;<br />
<br />
Alonso: &quot;You had to keep him close, as close as I could because I knew he was going to be a good influence for me.&quot;

Divock Origi has defended his Liverpool record and vowed to re-launch his Anfield career after his season-long loan at Wolfsburg.<br />
<br />
Origi: &quot;You can&rsquo;t expect for a youngster to perform consistently. It went with ups and with downs. I scored 21 goals in two years. Not bad.&quot;
